steps.title: Create a Python sandbox to work in
Search for and download World Bank data on gross savings as % of GDP
Process the data to identify countries meeting the criteria
Format the final answer as requested

content:
# Conversation Summary

The conversation focused on identifying countries with gross savings exceeding 35% of GDP for every year from 2001-2010 according to World Bank data. Multiple approaches were attempted to access the World Bank API and data, including:

1. Creating Python sandboxes to access World Bank data through various API methods
2. Attempting to download bulk data from the World Bank
3. Using a browsing agent to search for and analyze the data

After several attempts with different API formats and approaches, the browsing agent successfully retrieved the data and identified the countries meeting the criteria.

# Final Answer

$\boxed{Algeria, Bahrain, Brunei Darussalam, China, Gabon, Iran, Islamic Republic of, Malaysia, Macao SAR China, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Singapore}$
